{meta: title Gathering In The Sky}
{meta: artist Porter Wagoner}
{meta: composer Wayne Raney and R.E. Winsett}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]There'll be a great gathering in the sky 
When all of God's children get [C]home
We'll join the happy millions as they [G]sing 
There [A7]around the great white [D7]throne
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G]I'm speaking of a big camp meeting 
Where we never shall [C]say goodbye
I'm longing for the day when I hear my Savior [G]say 
There's a [D7]gathering in the [G]sky
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
One by one we pass through the valley
Then our load seems hard to [C]bear
But I'm going to a great [G]reunion 
Where [A7]people's not afraid of [D7]prayer
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[G]There'll be a lot of old time singing 
Somewhere up there on [C]high
It seems that I can hear them [G]saying 
There's a [D7]gathering in the [G]sky
{end_of_verse}

